    <div class="smaller-width">
      <p>One common mistake is to assume colors can do the job for actions such as showing valid or invalid inputs.</p> <p>In most color
      blind types, the green and red outlines are either confused together, or not matching any code color reminding of a valid or invalid element (grey, yellows. etc.)</p>
      <p>Learn more: <a href="https://uxplanet.org/designing-ecommerce-for-colourblind-users-1ffd648c9f91#3-avoid-communicating-a-message-on-the-basis-of-colour" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Avoid communicating a message on the basis of colour</a></p>
    </div>
  </div>

