  <h3 align="right">Color pickers</h3>
  <div class="container-right">
    <div align="left">
      <p>Color pickers sometimes use the original color as caption. This type of selection is only accessible for non colorblind users. Users with protanopia, deuternopia, tritanopia and achromatopsia are unable to identify the original colors shown. </p>
      <p>With protanopia and deuteranopia, reds, greens, yellows, purple are impossible to identify. Tritan users will confuse pinks, yellows, purple, also, greens and blues are altered and difficult to identify.</p>
      <p>Learn more: <a href="https://uxplanet.org/designing-ecommerce-for-colourblind-users-1ffd648c9f91" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Designing eCommerce for colorblind users</a></p>
    </div>
