    <div align="left">
      <p>Pie charts and graphics are also easily inaccessible, due to the colors, again, being the only source of information. Different tones of blue and yellow will be seen as very similar with protanopia, deuteranopia, tritanopia. Achromatopsia can even show colors in the same shade of grey, which makes the pie chart impossible to read.</p>
